# Pre-commit Hook Rules

## Code Quality Checks
- Run linters for all modified files
- Check for syntax errors in code files
- Validate JSON and YAML files
- Ensure no debugger statements in code
- Check for console.log statements in production code

## Security Checks
- Scan for hardcoded credentials
- Check for exposed API keys
- Validate no sensitive information in commits
- Ensure no private keys or certificates are committed

## File Checks
- Verify no large binary files (>10MB)
- Check for trailing whitespace
- Ensure files end with newline
- Validate file permissions are correct
- Check for merge conflict markers

## Testing Requirements
- Run unit tests for modified files
- Ensure test coverage meets minimum threshold
- Validate no broken tests

## Documentation
- Check for missing documentation in new functions
- Ensure README updates for new features
- Validate markdown formatting

## Project Specific
- Ensure package-lock.json is updated with package.json
- Check for unused dependencies
- Validate import statements